!! Introduction

The ''TiddlyWiki Developer Tools'' plugin is part of the [[WikiLabs|https://wikilabs.github.io/]] collection of plugins for TiddlyWiki. It adds powerful browser-side inspection capabilities, helping you understand how rendered output maps back to wikitext source — across transclusion boundaries, macros, procedures, and list widgets.

!! Key Features

|! Feature |! Description |
|! [[Hover Tooltip]] |Hover any element to see its source position, context, and transclusion caller chain |
|! [[Context Menu]] |Right-click any element for copy options, navigation, source viewing, and editing |
|! [[Source Viewer]] |A floating panel that accumulates source code entries with deduplication and origin highlighting |
|! [[Variable Inspector]] |Inspect all variables in scope at any element — with filtering, type badges, and previews |
|! [[Inline Editor]] |Edit wikitext source directly in a floating popup (optional) |

!! Quick Start

# Enable source position tracking: ''Control Panel'' &rarr; ''Settings'' &rarr; ''Source Position Tracking'' &rarr; check the box
# ''Save and reload'' the page
# ''Hover'' over any element to see its source position tooltip
# ''Right-click'' any element to open the context menu with more options

See [[Configuration]] for all available settings.

!! How It Works

The plugin uses TiddlyWiki's hook system — ''zero overhead when disabled'':

* `th-dom-rendering-element` — tracks HTML elements
* `th-dom-rendering-link` — tracks link elements
* `th-dom-rendering-codeblock` — tracks code blocks
* Monkey-patches the transclude widget to track source context across transclusion boundaries

Line numbers in the `data-source-pos` attribute are ''file-ready'' — they include the `.tid` file header offset so they match what your editor shows.

!! Interactions at a Glance

|! Action |! Effect |
| ''Hover'' |Tooltip with source position and caller chain |
| ''Right-click'' |DevTools context menu |
| ''Ctrl+click'' |Navigate directly to source tiddler |
| ''Ctrl+right-click'' |Native browser context menu (passthrough) |

!! Useful With

* Works best in combination with an MCP-server for editor integration
* Useful for any TiddlyWiki developer investigating template rendering

